ntroduced the case game in December 2002 after a 15-month hiatus of the show.\n\n[[V\u00e9ronique Landry]] is the only model to appear on more than one version of the show, on both the French and English Canadian versions.{{Citation needed|date=April 2007}}  [[Howie Mandel]], [[H\u00e9ctor Sandarti]], and [[Linda de Mol]] each have hosted multiple versions of the show: Mandel, with the [[American English]] and [[Canadian English]] versions, Sandarti with both the [[Spanish in the United States|American Spanish]] and [[Mexican Spanish]] versions, and de Mol with both the Netherlands Dutch and German (in 2004) versions of the show. In the UK version ''Deal Or No Deal'' helped relaunch [[Noel Edmonds]]'s career.\n\n==Top prize winners==\nAll amounts below the prizes are their equivalents in [[United States dollar]]s at the time of their win.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Country !! Name(s) !! Date !! Amount won !! Previous offer !! Other amount !! Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=3 | {{Flagicon|Afghanistan}} [[Ganjina|'''''\u06af\u0646\u062c\u06cc\u0646'''/'''Ganjina''''']] || Mohammad Easa Sediqi || Prior to October 25, 2010 || [[Afghan afghani|Af.]] 1,000,000<br />($23,240) || Box Swap<br>(declined) || Af. 2,500<br />($58.10) || <ref>{{YouTube|id=Gdk-_wF9dCQ}}</ref><ref>{{in lang|de}}[http://www.spiegel.de/video/deal-or-no-deal-gluecksspiel-auf-afghanisch-video-1090784.html \"Deal or No Deal\": Gl\u00fccksspiel auf afghanisch (\"Deal or No Deal\": Gambling in Afghanistan)], October 25, 2010</ref><br />First top prize winner in Afghan history\n|-\n| (unknown) || Prior to November 28, 2012 || [[Afghan afghani|Af.]] 1,000,000<br />($19,569) || Af. 342,000<br />($6,693) || Af. 10,000<br />($196) || <ref>[http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=545919262089410 Photo from the official Facebook page of Tolo TV], November 28, 2012</ref><br>The banker first offered Af. 311,000, then Af. 342,000, then a chance to swap the boxes. All were declined. Rebroadcast June 5, 2013.\n|-\n