nott]], 25, English footballer ([[Altrincham F.C.|Altrincham]], [[F.C. Halifax Town|Halifax Town]]), victim of assault.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thenorthernecho.co.uk/news/national/18187455.matlock-town-footballer-dies-hospital-late-night-assault/|title=Matlock Town footballer dies in hospital after late night assault|publisher=Northern Echo|date=25 January 2020|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>\n*27 January \u2013 [[Derek Edwards (rugby league)|Derek Edwards]], British rugby league player ([[Castleford Tigers|Castleford]], [[Great Britain national rugby league team|national team]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rugbyleaguecares.org/news/general/rl-mourns-death-1970-lion-derek-edwards/|title=RL mourns death of 1970 Lion Derek Edwards|publisher=Rugby League Cares|date=28 January 2020|access-date=28 January 2020}}</ref>\n*28 January\n**[[Paul Farnes]], 101, [[Royal Air Force|RAF]] pilot and [[World War II]] veteran, last surviving ace of the [[Battle of Britain]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Humphries|first=Will|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/paul-farnes-last-battle-of-britain-ace-dies-aged-101-thxl6k2vn|title=Paul Farnes, last Battle of Britain ace, dies aged 101|work=The Times|date=29 January 2020|access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Nicholas Parsons]], 96, actor (''[[Four Feather Falls]]''), radio and television presenter (''[[Just a Minute]]'', ''[[Sale of the Century (British game show)|Sale of the Century]]''), [[Rector of the University of St Andrews]] (1988\u20131991).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-11808907|title=Obituary: Nicholas Parsons|date=28 January 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=28 January 2020|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n**[[Peter Rogers (businessman)|Peter Rogers]], 72, businessman ([[Babcock International]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.babcockinternational.com/news/tribute-to-peter-rogers/|title=Tribute to Peter Rogers|publisher=Babcock International|date=10 February 2020|access-date=16 February 202