alist)|Jack Schofield]] in 2009]]\n*2 March \u2013 [[Bahamian Bounty]], 26, racehorse and sire.<ref>{{cite web|title=Group 1 hero Bahamian Bounty dies aged 26 at the National Stud|url=https://www.racingpost.com/bloodstock/bloodstock-latest/group-1-hero-bahamian-bounty-dies-aged-26-at-the-national-stud/425792|website=Racing Post|date=2 March 2020}}</ref> (death announced on this date)\n*4 March \u2013 [[David Bentley (bishop of Gloucester)|David Bentley]], 84, Anglican prelate, [[Bishop of Gloucester]] (1993\u20132003).<ref>[http://epaper.thetimes.co.uk/epaper/viewer.aspx Bentley]</ref>\n*6 March\n**[[Peter Smith (bishop)|Peter Smith]], 76, Roman Catholic prelate, Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of East Anglia|East Anglia]] (1995\u20132001), Archbishop of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cardiff|Cardiff]] (2001\u20132010) and [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Southwark|Southwark]] (2010\u20132019).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wilson|first1=John|title=Archbishop Peter Smith has died|url=https://www.indcatholicnews.com/news/39076|website=Independent Catholic News|date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Patrick Wright, Baron Wright of Richmond]], 88, diplomat and life peer.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lord Wright of Richmond obituary|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/lord-wright-of-richmond-obituary-pbrkxxr5f|work=The Times|date=9 March 2020}} {{paywall}}</ref>\n*7 March\n**[[John Manners (cricketer)|John Manners]], 105, [[Royal Navy]] officer and cricketer ([[Hampshire County Cricket Club|Hampshire]], [[Marylebone Cricket Club|Marylebone]]).<ref>{{cite news|title=Lieutenant Commander John Manners, naval officer who sank a U-boat and played cricket for Hampshire \u2013 obituary|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/obituaries/2020/03/09/lieutenant-commander-john-manners-naval-officer-sank-u-boat/|work=The Telegraph|date=9 March 2020}} {{registration required}}</ref>\n**[[Matthew Watkins]], 41, Welsh rugby union player ([[Newport RFC|Newport]], [[Scarlets]], [[Wales national rugby union team|n