stein-dead.html|title=Peter Kirstein, Father of the European Internet, Is Dead at 86|work=The New York Times|date=8 January 2020|access-date=10 January 2020}}</ref>\n**[[David Montgomery, 2nd Viscount Montgomery of Alamein]], 91, peer and businessman, member of the [[House of Lords]] (1976\u20131999, 2005\u20132015).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://announcements.telegraph.co.uk/deaths/238707/montgomery|title=Montgomery|publisher=Daily Telegraph: Announcements|date=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n*9 January\n**[[The Alexander Brothers|Tom Alexander]], 85, musician ([[The Alexander Brothers]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-51064069|title=Tom Alexander of The Alexander Brothers dies aged 85|work=BBC News|date=10 January 2020|access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n**[[John Brownjohn]], 90, literary translator.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://announcements.telegraph.co.uk/deaths/238583/brownjohn|title=Brownjohn|publisher=Daily Telegraph: Announcements|date=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Jimmy Shields (footballer)|Jimmy Shields]], 88, Northern Irish footballer ([[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], [[Oxford United F.C.|Headington United]], [[Northern Ireland national football team|national team]]).<ref>{{cite news|last=Bull|first=David|url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/news/2020-01-10/obituary-jimmy-shields-southampton-football-club|title=Jimmy Shields: An appreciation|publisher=Southampton F.C.|date=10 January 2020|access-date=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n*10 January\n**[[Alun Gwynne Jones, Baron Chalfont]], 100, politician, [[Minister of State for Foreign Affairs (United Kingdom)|Minister of State for Foreign Affairs]] (1964\u20131970) and member of the [[House of Lords]] (1964\u20132015).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/lord-chalfont-obituary-r5r3mgz8d|title=Lord Chalfont obituary|work=The Times|date=14 January 2020}} {{paywall}}</ref>\n**[[Roddy Lumsden]], 53, poet.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloodaxebooks.com/news?articleid=1006|title=Rodd