ir disaster]] survivor.<ref>{{cite news|title=Harry Gregg: Sir Bobby Charlton leads tributes to late Manchester United great|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51530864|work=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n*17 February \u2013 [[Andrew Weatherall]], 56, music producer (''[[Screamadelica]]''), disc jockey and musician ([[The Sabres of Paradise]], [[Two Lone Swordsmen]]).<ref>{{cite news|last1=Savage|first1=Mark|title=DJ and producer Andrew Weatherall dies |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51535685|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n*19 February\n**[[Heather Couper]], 70, astronomer and broadcaster, President of the [[British Astronomical Association]] (1984\u20131986).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51562165|title=Heather Couper: Broadcaster and astronomer dies at 70|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=20 February 2020|access-date=22 February 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Wilfred De'ath]], 82, journalist (''[[The Oldie]]'').<ref>{{cite news|last=Cook|first=William|url=https://www.theoldie.co.uk/blog/rip-wilfred-death-1937-2020|title=RIP Wilfred De'Ath (1937\u20132020)|work=The Oldie|date=20 February 2020|access-date=22 February 2020}}</ref>\n*20 February\n**[[Malcolm Pyke]], 81, English footballer ([[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], [[Dartford F.C.|Dartford]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2020/february/20-february/malcolm-pyke-1938-2020|title=Malcolm Pyke 1938\u20132020|publisher=West Ham United|date=20 February 2020|access-date=22 February 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Jimmy Wheeler (footballer)|Jimmy Wheeler]], 86, English footballer ([[Reading F.C.|Reading]]) and football manager ([[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2020/february/jimmy-wheeler-1933-2020/|title=Jimmy Wheeler 1933\u20132020|publisher=Reading F.C.|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n*22 Februar